The Tshwane metro has resolved to part ways with its controversial city manager Moeketsi Mosola. JOHANNESBURG - The Tshwane metro has resolved to part ways with its controversial city manager, Moeketsi Mosola. It's believed taxpayers will be forking out as much as R7-million for Mosola to walk away. Tshwane mayor Stevens Mokgalapa has admitted to friction between the city and political office bearers. READ: City of Tshwane, Municipal Manager part ways He says it's had a negative effect on service delivery. The council has appointed chief audit executive Moeketsi Ntsimane as acting city manager. There's also been no mention of whether action will be taken against Mosola over the controversial Glad-Africa contract.